<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,151,938]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,805,830]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is very similar to species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[940,1067,805,830]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Relictanum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Diptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen.nov.">
<emphasis box="[940,1067,805,830]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Relictanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1077,1175,806,830]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="genus">gen.nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but it is distinguished from that genus by the presence of a second row of shorter pile on the dorsal occiput, and by genitalic characters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,151,938]" box="[199,994,877,902]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
This species corresponds to sp 
<quantity box="[539,596,877,902]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3716" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="in" value="54.0">54 in</quantity>
the cladograms of Miranda (
<number box="[921,981,878,902]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="2011.0">2011</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
